@startuml BidHub Runtime View 3 of 3 - Infrastructure Registration
!theme plain
skinparam componentFontSize 13
skinparam packageFontSize 14
skinparam noteFontSize 11
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 20
skinparam ranksep 60

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor<<FunctionalMicroservice>>     #FFE0B2
    BorderColor<<FunctionalMicroservice>>         #A80036
    BackgroundColor<<InfrastructureMicroservice>> #E0E0E0
    BorderColor<<InfrastructureMicroservice>>     #616161
}

title **BidHub — Runtime View (3 / 3)**\n//Infrastructure plane — Eureka service discovery + Spring Cloud Config bootstrap.//\nLEMMA Operation viewpoint, Fig. 3 Lakeside-Mutual style (Sorgalla et al., 2021).\nOwner: Mykola Vaskevych (22372199)

' ============================================================
' INFRASTRUCTURE COMPONENTS (top centre)
' ============================================================
component "<<Infrastructure Microservice>>\n**Eureka Server**\n(Spring Cloud Netflix)\n:8761" as Eureka <<InfrastructureMicroservice>>
component "<<Infrastructure Microservice>>\n**Config Server**\n(Spring Cloud Config)\n:8888" as Config <<InfrastructureMicroservice>>

' ============================================================
' CLIENT SERVICES (bottom, grouped in one package)
' ============================================================
package "All 8 BidHub services (7 functional + API gateway)" as Clients <<Rectangle>> {
    component "<<Infrastructure Microservice>>\n**api-gateway**\n:8080" as Gateway <<InfrastructureMicroservice>>
    component "<<Functional Microservice>>\n**user-service**\n:8081" as User <<FunctionalMicroservice>>
    component "<<Functional Microservice>>\n**catalog-service**\n:8082" as Catalogue <<FunctionalMicroservice>>
    component "<<Functional Microservice>>\n**auction-service**\n:8083" as Auction <<FunctionalMicroservice>>
    component "<<Functional Microservice>>\n**order-service**\n:8084" as Order <<FunctionalMicroservice>>
    component "<<Functional Microservice>>\n**payment-service**\n:8085" as Payment <<FunctionalMicroservice>>
    component "<<Functional Microservice>>\n**notification-service**\n:8086" as Notif <<FunctionalMicroservice>>
    component "<<Functional Microservice>>\n**admin-service**\n:8087" as Admin <<FunctionalMicroservice>>
}

' ============================================================
' AGGREGATED ARROWS — one per direction, from the package boundary.
' Every service in the package performs both flows; showing 8 x 2
' individual arrows would overwhelm the diagram, so the pattern is
' expressed aggregately and the accompanying note enumerates it.
' ============================================================
Clients -[#0277BD,bold]--> Eureka : "**http** — register on startup\n+ periodic heartbeat\n(all 8 services)"
Clients -[#388E3C,bold,dashed]--> Config : "**http** — bootstrap config\nat startup\n(all 8 services)"

' ============================================================
' EXPANDED LISTING NOTE
' ============================================================
note right of Eureka
    **Eureka registration — per-service**
    ————————————————————
    Each of the 8 services above:
    • Registers its `spring.application.name` +
      host/port with Eureka on startup.
    • Sends periodic heartbeat (default 30 s)
      to stay in the registry.
    • Uses `lb://<service-id>` URIs (resolved
      via Eureka) for all cross-service REST
      calls — no hard-coded host:port anywhere.

    **api-gateway** additionally **discovers**
    downstream routes via Eureka (see Runtime
    View 1/3 for the request-path arrows).
end note

note right of Config
    **Config Server bootstrap — per-service**
    ———————————————————————
    At application startup, every service (and
    the API gateway) fetches its profile-specific
    YAML from Config Server **before** building
    the Spring application context.

    Profile files (one per service, in
    `backend/config-server/src/main/resources/config/`):
    • `api-gateway-dev.yml`
    • `user-service-dev.yml`
    • `catalog-service-dev.yml`
    • `auction-service-dev.yml`
    • `order-service-dev.yml`
    • `payment-service-dev.yml`
    • `notification-service-dev.yml`
    • `admin-service-dev.yml`

    Bootstrap is a **startup-only** flow (dashed),
    not a hot-reload path in our current setup.
end note

' ============================================================
' LEGEND
' ============================================================
legend bottom left
    **Infrastructure registration — this diagram**
    —————————————————————————
    | Colour | Protocol flow |
    | <#0277BD> | Eureka registration + heartbeat (solid, continuous) |
    | <#388E3C> | Config Server bootstrap (dashed, startup-only) |
    ——
    The pattern is homogeneous across all 8 services;
    per Sorgalla 2021 §Background, each microservice
    is independently deployable and discovers peers
    through Eureka rather than through hard-coded URLs.
    ——
    **This is 3 of 3 runtime views.** See also:
    • `runtime_view_1_sync.puml` — HTTP request path
    • `runtime_view_2_async.puml` — AMQP event flows
endlegend

@enduml
